TGT Reference Manual: Functions

NAME

tgt_hide
tgt_unhide -  Make an object invisible and unselectable

SYNOPSIS

void tgt_hide(struct tgt_object * obj);
void tgt_unhide(struct tgt_object * obj);

DESCRIPTION

tgt_hide hides an object and makes it unselectable, which means the focus cannot be set on it
tgt_unhide makes the object visible and selectable again

Those functions refresh properly objects and their parents, when necessary.
